T1  - Product diversity, endogenous markups, and development traps
AU  - Gali, Jordi
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 36
IS  - 1
SP  - 39
EP  - 63
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/08/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(95)01209-8
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393295012098
KW  - Multiple equilibria
KW  - Growth models
KW  - Endogenous markups
KW  - Convergence
AB  - We analyze the implications of endogenous markups for the dynamics of capital accumulation, in an environment in which the degree of competition increases with economic development. In equilibrium, markups are inversely related to the aggregate capital stock, which makes it possible for the marginal revenue product of capital to be nonmonotonic, even if the marginal product of capital is strictly diminishing. That feature raises the possibility of multiple steady states and, most interestingly, multiple equilibrium paths (converging to different steady states) for given initial conditions. We conclude by discussing some of the predictions of our model and assessing their empirical relevance.
ER  - 

