KW  - Structural equations
KW  - Virtual/traditional fundamentals
KW  - Volatility
KW  - Monetary models
KW  - Fixed/floating exchange rate regimes
AB  - Fixed exchange rates are less volatile than floating rates. But the volatility of macroeconomic variables such as money and output does not change very much across exchange rate regimes. This suggests that exchange rate models based only on macroeconomic fundamentals are unlikely to be very successful. It also suggests that there is no clear tradeoff between reduced exchange rate volatility and macroeconomic stability.
ER  - 
